<p class="newssubhead_t1">Fertilizer prices on the rise</p>

According to DTN, anhydrous surged 23 percent in August compared to a month earlier.  DTN&rsquo;s end-of-August survey showed the average price for anhydrous is now over 606 dollars per ton.  That&rsquo;s up from 466 dollars per ton nine weeks ago.  And it&rsquo;s 41 percent higher than one year ago.<br />
UAN solutions and phosphorus fertilizers were also higher, up 7 to 12 percent compared to a month earlier.  Just one fertilizer slipped lower in August&mdash;potash was down 6 percent compared to a month earlier, with an average price of 466 per ton.
